.TH man 3 "14 april 2021" "Holberton School 0x16.C - Simple_Shell"

.SH NAME
Simple_Shell - command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
#include "holberton.h"

.SH Sintaxis
int main(int argc, char *argv[])

.SH format
This is the string that contains the text to be written to stdout.
#include <stdarg.h>

.SH DESCRIPTION
shell is a computer program which exposes an operating
system's services to a human user or other program.
In general, operating system shells use either a command-line
interface or graphical user interface, depending on a computer's role
and particular operation.

.SH Return Value
simple_shell() when it returns 0 the execution was done perfectly

.B exit
Terminates the calling process immediately.

.B ctrl + D
Terminates the calling process immediately.

.B ctrl + C
interrupts operation

.B env
show the enviroment

.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
Shell(1)

.SH BUGS
you can't handle pipes,
semicolon is not handled,
can't change current directory.

.SH AUTHOR
Alexander Forero, Daniel Escobar and Luis Mejia
